The Warrior gave strength to their arms, whilst the Smith wrought
for each a suit of iron plates.”,
“Your Smith must have been Rhoynish,”, Illyrio quipped.

There was an agelessness about him, a stillness;
on Roose Bolton’s face, rage and joy looked much the same.All he
and Ramsay had in common were their eyes.

Old Flint and The Norrey had been given places of high honor just
below the dais.Both men had been too old to march with Stannis;
they had sent their sons and grandsons in their stead.

Reek might have done it.Would have done it, in hopes it might
please Lord Ramsay.These whores meant to steal Ramsay’s bride;
Reek could not allow that.
